</div>Why apologize to me? I feel the same way. I grew up as a Witness, and thus have a basic understanding of their beliefs -- good and bad. I'm not going to pollute the discussion with a sidetrack on this, but I have a great deal of respect for the _good_ (both beliefs and people) and a unique wrath for the bad. I don't practice anymore, nor really keep in touch.<br />
<br />
Grindel has said most of what I would re: the primary topic of this thread. Pretend I said what he said, but don't stop listening to him by association. <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /> I just want to add that Lunal is right -- Witnesses are well aware that they may die due to refusing a transfusion in some cases. They go into it expecting the worst, hoping for the best, and very, VERY afraid that someone will take away their right to refuse treatment.<br />
<br />
BTW: *hands extra aiches to some folks* <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" /></div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				<center><i>Our society's problem: Too Much Violence + Not Enough Sexual Content.</i></center>
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		

		

		

	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2" style="border: 1px solid #D1D1E1; border-top: 0px">
